reviews.review: This was a thrilling, satisfying ending to the Skywalker saga.  Will be seeing it again  and again

BEST STAR WARS YET. this movie will check off every box on your end-of-saga checklist and more. starts with action and doesn't let up until the credits roll. lucasfilm did a perfect job of answering every question but still leaving your mind to wander. george lucas would be proud. if you are just a movie fan, this movie will still keep you on the edge of your seat. you won't regret seeing this movie.

42 years. That’s how long it has been since the first Star Wars movie. The Skywalker Saga has been a long and amazing series that’s spanned over decades. The Rise of Skywalker had 42 years of that Saga to cover, and it does it well. Develop your opinion about how it should have ended but know that in TROS, you will ride the nostalgia that brought us this amazing series in the first place. And in the end, remember how much joy this series has brought to you as a child and now as a grown adult. The movie was excellent.
Honestly very enjoyable, and this is comic from someone who reads/watches/play every piece of star wars media, not some lousy critic.
Wow just sucked. I couldn't follow any of it horrible writing. If you want to see this be ready to sit brain in hand and just enjoy the colors, it's the best option other than not seeing it.

This was one of the greatest Theatrical experiences I have ever had. Second only to End game. It was amazing. Emotional. Nonstop action. I couldn't have asked for a better conclusion to the Skywalker Saga. The only problem.... now I want more!!!

A beautiful wrap to the trilogy. Although this shouldn't have been a problem in the first place, it did a wonderful job of correcting the mistakes of The Last Jedi, and did many characters right. As a lifelong Star Wars fan, I truly recommend watching this film, and not letting the hate of The Last Jedi blind you from the beauty of this movie. May the Force be with you all!

A fulfilling and happy ending to an amazing saga. This movie was much better than The Last Jedi and showed why Star Wars is truly amazing. Rey is an amazing character and I hope she has her own spinoff or movie after this.
